      "text": "==> CI/CD pipeline with AWS code commit ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "==> CI/CD pipeline with AWS code commit ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ieBSpbGtVrGBhMjUODhEa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1384.5885045366172,
      "y": 10816.060935606614,
      "width": 1077.0157714858651,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3B",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1972949088,
      "version": 290,
      "versionNonce": 313755744,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779126089581,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "==> Both are the same, but the terminology is different. Rather than everything is the same, \n    instead of using the open source tools, AWS is providing its own tools to integrate complete integration CI/CD. \n\n==> One important note here is we can use Ansible or Chef or puppet to push the latest build to the EC2 instance, \n        but Ansible and shell scripts are outdated, so we are using argo cd to push the latest changes to the EC2 instance. \n\nKey Terminologies in Open Source System vs IWS CI/CD \n\n1. Git = aws Code commit\n\n2. Jenkis = aws pipeline\n    \n3. Jenkins jobs = aws build\n\n4. Argo cd = aws cd\n\n5. at last we push code to ec2 instance",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "==> Both are the same, but the terminology is different. Rather than everything is the same, \n    instead of using the open source tools, AWS is providing its own tools to integrate complete integration CI/CD. \n\n==> One important note here is we can use Ansible or Chef or puppet to push the latest build to the EC2 instance, \n        but Ansible and shell scripts are outdated, so we are using argo cd to push the latest changes to the EC2 instance. \n\nKey Terminologies in Open Source System vs IWS CI/CD \n\n1. Git = aws Code commit\n\n2. Jenkis = aws pipeline\n    \n3. Jenkins jobs = aws build\n\n4. Argo cd = aws cd\n\n5. at last we push code to ec2 instance",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
